d_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kyleam/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kyleam/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kyleam/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kyleam/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kyleam/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kyleam/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2018-10-04T14:21:24Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-13T22:41:05Z", "closed_at": "2020-04-13T22:41:05Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "#### What is the problem?\r\nApparently the recently added to annex ability to retry failed downloads is disabled ([annex.retry defaults to 0](http://git-annex.branchable.com/bugs/some_transfers_for_get_-J4_fail_over_ssh__47__rsync_and_require_retry/#comment-cd8d46adf300f4b92a2caca6c6f5e803)) by default.  I first thought that we could just hardcode to provide e.g. `-c annex.retry=3` to all annex calls (`self._ANNEX_GIT_COMMON_OPTIONS`), but then thought that we better have a config setting for it defaulting to 3, BUT this is already git-annex'es config setting, which might be set and we would be forcefully overriding it.  So I wondered what should be our course of action?\r\n\r\nI think we could \r\n- define `datalad.annex.retry` common_cfg defaulting to 3 and describing that it would be used ONLY if configuration is not defining `annex.retry` config option\r\n- set it in `AnnexRepo.__init__` conditional as described above\r\n\r\nSounds like a reasonable plan or am I missing something?", "closed_by": {"login": "yarikoptic", "id": 39889, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39889?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic", "html_url": "https://github.com/yarikoptic", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/followe